PindouVerse — Licensing Overview
================================

Copyright (c) 2026 PindouVerse (cangelzz)

This project uses TWO licenses, depending on what you are looking at:

1. **Source code** (everything except `samples/`) is licensed under the
   **PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0**. See `LICENSE-CODE` for the
   full text.

2. **Sample bead-art designs** in `samples/` (the `*.pindou` files and
   accompanying images) are licensed under the
   **Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License
   (CC BY-NC 4.0)**. See `samples/LICENSE` for details.

Both licenses prohibit Commercial Use without a separate commercial license.

What counts as Commercial Use
-----------------------------

Commercial Use means any use intended for or directed toward commercial
advantage or monetary compensation. Examples that ARE Commercial Use:

- Selling, sublicensing, or hosting the software, its source code, or
  derivative works (whether stand-alone or bundled in another product).
- Offering the software, its features, or its file conversion capabilities
  as a paid service or as part of a paid SaaS / cloud offering.
- Operating the software inside a for-profit business as part of revenue-
  generating workflows (commercial bead-art studios, bead-design services,
  classes / camps charging for instruction that uses the software, etc.).
- Reproducing or distributing the sample `.pindou` designs (or images
  derived from them) for sale, advertising, or any commercial promotion.

What does NOT count as Commercial Use
-------------------------------------

The following are explicitly permitted under this license without paying
for a commercial license:

- Personal hobby use, study, research, and amateur pursuits.
- Use by schools, libraries, charities, public research / safety / health /
  environmental organizations, and government institutions (per PolyForm
  Noncommercial 1.0.0 §"Noncommercial Organizations").
- **Individuals using the software to design and physically produce their
  own bead artwork, and then selling that finished physical artwork.**
  Selling the resulting bead artwork that you made by hand is NOT, by
  itself, Commercial Use of this software. This clarification applies to
  the software only; the sample blueprint designs in `samples/` remain
  separately governed by CC BY-NC 4.0 and may not be redistributed or
  used as the basis for commercial designs without a separate license.

Commercial Licensing
--------------------

If you want to use this software or the sample designs in a way that
exceeds the permissions above, a separate commercial license is required.
Open a GitHub issue at https://github.com/cangelzz/pindouverse/issues with
the label `commercial-license` describing your intended use, or contact
the project owner via the contact details on the repository.

Earlier Releases
----------------

Versions of this project that were distributed under the MIT license
(through 0.8.9 inclusive) continue to be available under MIT — that grant
is irrevocable. This new license applies to versions published from
0.8.10 onward and to all later contributions.

Notices
-------

When redistributing this software (only as permitted by the licenses
above), you must include both `LICENSE` and `LICENSE-CODE` in their
entirety, along with the following required notice:

    Required Notice: Copyright (c) 2026 PindouVerse — Licensed under
    PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0. See LICENSE-CODE.
